text: Annika Virpi Irene Saarikko (born 10 November 1983) is a Finnish politician and minister. On 5 September 2020, she was elected as the leader of the Finnish Centre Party. In 2020, she became the Deputy Prime Minister of Finland. ==References== Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Deputy Prime Ministers of Finland
